# Project
The aim is for robust, private, useful software.
Full Stack Functional F#

We are working through [[doc/plan]].

In markdown files reference files using the format  [[workspace_path/filename.ext]]

## How to work
Maximum 100 lines of change (total diff) per request.  Prefer less.  If a request would require more than that, instead write a plan describing the change so we can work at smaller increments.

If a requested course of action seems inefficient, stop and propose a more efficient course.
If a request is unclear, just ask.

Put non-trivial plans in a markdown file in doc/ so I can review.

Use Test Driven Development.
Write test - stop for review.  
Make test pass.  Stop for review.  
Refactor.  Stop for review.

Don't bother using git unless asked a history or status question.  I will take care of git.

## Source code
Maximum 100 characters per line.
Follow language norms.
TABs are not allowed in F#
Always indent 4 spaces.
Indentation is AS important AS it is in python or Haskell.
If a function might fail, use Result types with errors, eschewing exceptions for things that should be handled (e.g. retries).

## Environment
Windows
GIT Bash shell
Occasionally the first time you send a command, the tool will delete the first character of your command.  If so, just send it again.
F# front and back end.  Client compiled with Fable for browser UI.  .NET for server.  Shared files should be compilable in either so use basic libraries only.
